==English==

===Etymology 1===
From [[Scandinavian]] ''troll'', supernatural being; probably related to Swedish ''[[trolla]]'' and Danish ''[[trylle]]'', to perform magical arts.

====Noun====
{{en-noun-reg}}

# A supernatural being, often represented as of diminutive size, but sometimes as a giant, and fabled to inhabit caves, hills, and like places; a witch.
# Colloquial: An ugly person of either sex.
# (''Internet'') A [[posting]] to a [[newsgroup]], [[bulletin board]], etc, that is deliberately intended to [[anger]] other [[poster]]s and cause [[argument]]s.
# A [[fishing]] term referring to [[trail]]ing a baited line.

