===Etymology 2===
Middle High German ''trollen'': to stroll through Old French ''troller'': to quest.

====Verb====
{{en-infl-reg-consonant|troll||}}

# To [[fish]] for fish using a line and bait.
# By extension: To search in desultory fashion. e.g. He trolled through the dictionary.
# Vulgar: To look for a sexual partner. e.g I am trolling for custom, said the actress to the Bishop.
#{{dated}} to follow [[soldier]]s for the purpose of [[prostitution]]

